<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
4. 
<taxonomicName LSID="1CB2C3A9-391A-5C67-967E-49331CF8354C" authority="(Blume) Pierre var. stenophylla Merr., Enum. Philipp. Fl. Pl. 70 (1923)." authorityName="(Blume) Pierre var. stenophylla Merr., Enum. Philipp. Fl. Pl. 70 (1923)." authorityYear="1923" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Theaceae" genus="Thea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Thea lanceolata" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceolata">Thea lanceolata (Blume) Pierre var. stenophylla Merr., Enum. Philipp. Fl. Pl. 70 (1923).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="lectotype">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Lectotype.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
(designated here): Philippines. Luzon: Ilocos Norte Province, Bangui to Claveria, August 1918, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">M. Ramos 33005</emphasis>
(US 00113903 [the image is available at http://n2t.net/ark:/65665/34f38884f-74b3-4f15-8e0b-db0f884e39b1]!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.49412" author="Merrill, ED" journalOrPublisher="Bureau of Printing, Manila" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" refId="B12" refString="Merrill, ED, 1923. An Enumeration of Philippine Flowering Plants (Vol. 3). Bureau of Printing, Manila, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.49412" title="An Enumeration of Philippine Flowering Plants (Vol. 3)." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.49412" year="1923">Merrill (1923</bibRefCitation>
: 70) cited a single collection, &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">B.S. 33005 Ramos</emphasis>
&quot; in the protologue without specifying the corresponding herbarium. Two duplicates of this gathering were found at K and US, so they are syntypes (Art. 40 Note 1 of the ICN) of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Theaceae" genus="T." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="T. lanceolata subsp. var. var. stenophylla" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="lanceolata" subSpecies="var." variety="stenophylla">T. lanceolata var. stenophylla</taxonomicName>
. The specimen at US bearing barcode 00113903 is selected above as the lectotype of this taxon because a fragment of fruit is attached on a branchlet of the sheet.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
Due to a lack of materials, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sealy, JR" journalOrPublisher="The Royal Horticultural Society, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" refId="B15" refString="Sealy, JR, 1958. A Revision of the Genus Camellia. The Royal Horticultural Society, London" title="A Revision of the Genus Camellia." year="1958">Sealy (1958</bibRefCitation>
: 145) did not give this variety a formal taxonomic treatment. 
<bibRefCitation author="Keng, H" journalOrPublisher="Gardens' Bulletin (Singapore)" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" pagination="65 - 69" refId="B11" refString="Keng, H, 1989. The genus Camellia (Theaceae) in Malesia, Florae Malesianae precursores - LVIII, part three. Gardens' Bulletin (Singapore) 42: 65 - 69" title="The genus Camellia (Theaceae) in Malesia, Florae Malesianae precursores - LVIII, part three." volume="42" year="1989">Keng (1989</bibRefCitation>
: 68) identified it as a heterotypic synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. lanceolata" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">C. lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Blume) Seem. and claimed that the latter was &quot;understandably unlikely to be a homogeneous taxon&quot; based on its widespread geographic distribution. I generally agree with 
<bibRefCitation author="Keng, H" journalOrPublisher="Gardens' Bulletin (Singapore)" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" pagination="65 - 69" refId="B11" refString="Keng, H, 1989. The genus Camellia (Theaceae) in Malesia, Florae Malesianae precursores - LVIII, part three. Gardens' Bulletin (Singapore) 42: 65 - 69" title="The genus Camellia (Theaceae) in Malesia, Florae Malesianae precursores - LVIII, part three." volume="42" year="1989">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Keng’s">Keng's</normalizedToken>
(1989)
</bibRefCitation>
broad circumscription of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. lanceolata" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">C. lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until more data are available (see below).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
